Sentencas: La-doped CeO2 nanoparticles of composition Ce1-xLaxO2-delta (0 <= x <= 0.1) have been studied here as prospective electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Synthesis, structure and ionic conductivity of nanocrystalline Ce1-xLaxO2-δ as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: They were synthesized by auto combustion method and the powder samples were calcined at 700 degrees C to get ultrafine nanocrystalline particles.
Titulo: Synthesis, structure and ionic conductivity of nanocrystalline Ce1-xLaxO2-δ as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: They were characterized by XRD, Raman, FTIR, XPS, DRS, FESEM/EDX, particle size analyzer and ac-impedance techniques.
Titulo: Synthesis, structure and ionic conductivity of nanocrystalline Ce1-xLaxO2-δ as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ionic conductivity was measured from 350 - 750 degrees C. The Ce0.90La0.1O2-delta (0.1 LDC) and Ce0.95La0.05O2-delta (0.05 LDC) showed a maximum conductivity of 8.89 x 10(-3) and 8.32 x 10(-3) S cm(-1) at 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Synthesis, structure and ionic conductivity of nanocrystalline Ce1-xLaxO2-δ as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
Synthesis, structure and ionic conductivity of nanocrystalline Ce1-xLaxO2-δ as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
Synthesis, structure and ionic conductivity of nanocrystalline Ce1-xLaxO2-δ as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The activation energy of 0.1 LDC and 0.05 LDC was found to be 0.70 eV and 0.87 eV, respectively.
Titulo: Synthesis, structure and ionic conductivity of nanocrystalline Ce1-xLaxO2-δ as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These values are higher than those reported for La doped CeO2 in literature.
Titulo: Synthesis, structure and ionic conductivity of nanocrystalline Ce1-xLaxO2-δ as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SOFC performance with 0.05 LDC as electrolyte showed open circuit voltage of 0.81 V and maximum power density of 41 mW cm(-2) at 650 degrees C using hydrogen as fuel.
Titulo: Synthesis, structure and ionic conductivity of nanocrystalline Ce1-xLaxO2-δ as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
